This paper deals with computer vision techniques for road segmentation using stereo cameras, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of advanced driver assistance systems, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves parameter estimation and optimization, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of Otsu's thresholding method, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM).
